name: Tihraqua Ahmed
resume_text:
Senior Quality Assurance Engineer with over 6 years of experience in fintech, telecom, government, and insurance. Specializes in API and regression testing, with expertise in test plans, Selenium Webdriver, and performance testing using JMETER. Skilled in Agile/Scrum methodologies for delivering high-quality software solutions. 

Professional Experience:
- Council of Health Insurance, Senior Quality Assurance Engineer, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia (Apr 2024 - Present)
  Developed and executed test plans and checklists, performed various testing methods, maintained Selenium Automation Frameworks, collaborated with teams.

- Zain Sudan, Applications QA & Testing Specialist, Khartoum, Sudan (Aug 2022 - May 2024)
  Developed and executed testing strategies, conducted performance testing, participated in application releases, and ensured service continuity and quality.

- Electronic Banking Services Co. EBS, Quality Assurance Engineer II, Khartoum, Sudan (Aug 2021 - Aug 2022)
  Developed test strategies, refined test cases, facilitated certification processes, and ensured software quality compliance.

- Electronic Banking Services Co. EBS, Quality Assurance Engineer, Khartoum, Sudan (Feb 2020 - Feb 2021)
  Executed test cases, ensured compliance with quality standards, and conducted reviews of product documentation.

Education:
- University of Khartoum, MSc. Industrial and Computational Mathematics
- University of Khartoum, BSc. Mathematics and Computer Science

Technical Skills: Selenium Webdriver, Appium, JMeter, Java, SQL, API Testing, Regression Testing, JIRA, TFS, Postman, CI/CD

Certifications:
- ISTQB® - FL Certificate
- ISTQB® - Mobile Application Tester Certificate

Languages: English (Native), Arabic (Native)
